    "owl": "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#",
    "xsd": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"
  },
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t5-1-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "thermodynamic temperature",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-1-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "T",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-1-1",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "Theta",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t5-1",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "5-1",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t5-1-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-1-0"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-1-1"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "partial derivative of internal energy with respect to entropy at constant volume and constant number of particles in the system:\n\n[stem%unnumbered]\n++++\nT = ((del U)/(del S))_(V,N)\n++++\n\nwhere stem:[U] is internal energy (<<t5-20.2>>), stem:[S] is entropy (<<t5-18>>), stem:[V] is volume (<<iso80000-3>>), and stem:[N] is number of particles\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "It is measured with a primary thermometer, examples of which are gas thermometers of different kinds, noise thermometers, or radiation thermometers.\n\nThe Boltzmann constant (<<iso80000-1>>) relates energy at the individual particle level with thermodynamic temperature.\n\nDifferences of thermodynamic temperatures or changes may be expressed either in kelvin, symbol stem:[\"unitsml(K)\"], or in de grees Celsius, symbol stem:[\"unitsml(degC)\"] (<<t5-2>>).\n\nThermodynamic temperature is one of the seven base quantities in the International System of Quantities, ISQ (see <<iso80000-1>>).\n\n*The International Temperature Scale of 1990*\n\nFor the purpose of practical measurements, the International Temperature Scale of 1990, ITS-90, was adopted by CIPM in 1989, which is a close approximation to the thermodynamic temperature scale.\n\nThe quantities defined by this scale are denoted stem:[T_\"90\"] and stem:[t_\"90\"], respectively (replacing stem:[T_\"68\"] and stem:[t_\"68\"] defined by the International Practical Temperature Scale of 1968, IPTS-68), where\n\n[stem%unnumbered]\n++++\n(t_\"90\")/(1 \"unitsml(degC)\") = (T_\"90\")/(1 \"unitsml(K)\") - 273.15\n++++\n\nThe units of stem:[T_\"90\"] and stem:[t_\"90\"] are the kelvin, symbol stem:[\"unitsml(K)\"], and the degree Celsius, symbol stem:[\"unitsml(degC)\"] (<<t5-2>>), respectively.\n\nFor further information, see <<its90>>, <<mepkelvin>>.\n\nFor ready conversion between temperatures reported on the International Temperature Scale and thermodynamic temperatures the systematic deviations can be found in <<estimates>>.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-K"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-5"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t5-2-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "Celsius temperature",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-2-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "t",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-2-1",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "vartheta",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t5-2",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "5-2",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t5-2-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-2-0"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-2-1"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "temperature difference from the thermodynamic temperature of the ice point is called the Celsius temperature stem:[t], which is defined by the quantity equation:\n\n[stem%unnumbered]\n++++\nt = T - T_\"0\"\n++++\n\nwhere stem:[T] is thermodynamic temperature (<<t5-1>>) and stem:[T_\"0\" = 273.15 \"unitsml(K)\"]\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "The unit degree Celsius is a special name for the kelvin for use in stating values of Celsius temperature. The unit degree Celsius is by definition equal in magnitude to the kelvin. A difference or interval of temperature may be expressed in kelvin or in degrees Celsius.\n\nThe thermodynamic temperature stem:[T_\"0\"] is stem:[0.01 \"unitsml(K)\"] below the thermodynamic temperature of the triple point of water.\n\nThe symbol stem:[\"unitsml(degC)\"] for the degree Celsius shall be preceded by a space (see <<iso80000-1>>).\n\nPrefixes are not allowed in combination with the unit stem:[\"unitsml(degC)\"].\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-degC"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-5"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t5-3.1-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "linear expansion coefficient",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-3.1-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "alpha_l",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t5-3.1",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "5-3.1",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t5-3.1-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-3.1-0"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "relative change of length with temperature:\n\n[stem%unnumbered]\n++++\nalpha_l = 1/l (\"d\"l)/(\"d\"T)\n++++\n\nwhere stem:[l] is length (<<iso80000-3>>) and stem:[T] is thermodynamic temperature (<<t5-1>>)\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "The subscripts in the symbols may be omitted when there is no risk of confusion.",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-K^(-1)"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-5"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t5-3.2-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "cubic expansion coefficient",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-3.2-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "alpha_V",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-3.2-1",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "gamma",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t5-3.2",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "5-3.2",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t5-3.2-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-3.2-0"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-3.2-1"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "relative change of volume with temperature:\n\n[stem%unnumbered]\n++++\nalpha_V = 1/V (\"d\"V)/(\"d\"T)\n++++\n\nwhere stem:[V] is volume (<<iso80000-3>>) and stem:[T] is thermodynamic temperature (<<t5-1>>)\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "Also called volumetric expansion coefficient.\n\nThe subscripts in the symbols may be omitted when there is no risk of confusion.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-K^(-1)"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-5"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t5-3.3-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "relative pressure coefficient",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-3.3-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "alpha_p",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t5-3.3",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "5-3.3",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t5-3.3-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-3.3-0"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "relative change of pressure with temperature at constant volume:\n\n[stem%unnumbered]\n++++\nalpha_p = 1/p ((del p)/(del T))_V\n++++\n\nwhere stem:[p] is pressure (<<iso80000-4>>), stem:[T] is thermodynamic temperature (<<t5-1>>), and stem:[V] is volume (<<iso80000-3>>)\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "The subscripts in the symbols may be omitted when there is no risk of confusion.",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-K^(-1)"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-5"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t5-4-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "pressure coefficient",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-4-0",
